## Task: Fix PR #6269

### Original PR Title: [antig] Port CR fallback logic to Skeptic Gates in worldarchitect.ai

### Original PR Description:
Ports the CodeRabbit fallback logic to the Skeptic Gates in worldarchitect.ai to fix a PR gating deadlock (specifically unblocking PR #6266). Allows the Skeptic Gates to pass if a formal `APPROVED` review state is missing but CodeRabbit posts an `[approve]` comment.

<!-- CURSOR_SUMMARY -->
---

> [!NOTE]
> **Medium Risk**
> Changes PR-merge gating logic in GitHub Actions; mistakes could incorrectly block or allow merges, though it’s limited to CI/workflow scripting and remains fail-closed in most error cases.
> 
> **Overview**
> **Gate-3 (CodeRabbit approval) logic is broadened and unified across workflows.** `green-gate.yml`, `skeptic-gate.yml`, `skeptic-cron.yml`, and `skeptic-evaluate.sh` now first check for a formal CodeRabbit `APPROVED` review, and if absent fall back to requiring *both* a current-head `CodeRabbit` commit status of `success` and a post-head bot comment containing `\[approve\]`.
> 
> **Approval detection is made more resilient.** The workflows now (a) consider CodeRabbit statuses regardless of state before evaluating the latest one, (b) loosen the approve-comment regex from “exact line match” to “match anywhere”, and (c) wrap the `gh | jq` pipelines with `set +e -o pipefail` and explicit exit-code handling, emitting a single `CR_SIGNAL` pass/fail message that drives eligibility.
> 
